<P><H1 align=center>ADD / EDIT MORTGAGE ACCOUNT – DC071</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>areas shown in red are mandatory and must be completed to 
proceed</FONT>           </P>
<P><H3>Owner of mortgage account: </H3>if it is a sole 
application, this field will be populated with the name of the applicant. If it 
is a joint application, select the relevant name against which to enter the 
details from the drop-down list
<P></P>
<P><H3>Mortgage account number: </H3>this field is not 
mandatory, however will be needed if a lenders reference is required
<P></P>
<P><H3>Do second charges apply?: </H3>click the ‘Yes’ or ‘No’ 
radio button depending on whether there are any second charges
<P></P>
<P><H3>Property Address: </H3>this field is a drop-down list 
consisting of the current address and any previous addresses entered. Select the 
relevant address from the list.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Others responsible?: </H3>if the current / previous 
mortgage is in joint names, click ‘Yes’ and enter the details in the field below
<P></P>
<P><H3>Lender Details (name, address, contact details): </H3>these will be required if a lender’s reference is to be obtained, to 
confirm that the conduct of the account was satisfactory
<P></P>
<P><STRONG>Note: </STRONG>the lender details may already be held and if so may be used to 
pre-populate the address fields, to check this click on ‘Directory’ (leads to 
Directory Search dialogue box – ZA020), and enter the lender’s name, town and 
sort code then click on ‘Directory Search’. The lender’s details will be shown 
in the box below – highlight the relevant lender and press ‘Select’. The 
dialogue box will then be closed and the lender’s details will then be populated 
in DC071.</P>
<P><H3>Indemnity Insurance Details: </H3>enter the indemnity 
insurance company, the <A href="HELP_FeesAssociatedWithMortgages.asp#MortgageIndemnenityFee">MIG</A> premium, the mortgage account and the date paid.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Loans: </H3>when these details have been completed, 
click on ‘Loans’ to enter further details of each mortgage account held. This 
leads to <A href="HELP_DC073.asp">Mortgage Loan Summary (DC073)</A>
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>Click OK to lead to next screen.
